name: src/PullExplorer.js
PullExplorer
description: PullExplorer allows the user to access and analyze GitHub pull request data.

name: constructor
description: PullExplorer is a class for parsing and exploring GitHub pull requests.

params.name: rawPullRequests
params.description:
The raw JSON object array for a GitHub repository's pull requests
as returned by https://api.github.org per the GitHub v3 API specification

name: pullRequests
description: An array of {@link PullRequest} objects created during PullExplorer initialization.

name: pullRequestCount
description: Returns the total number of pull requests.

name: getOldestCreationWeek
description: Returns how many weeks ago is the oldest date of pull request creation.

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description:
the number of weeks since `start` the oldest pull request was created at as an integer
rounded down

name: getNewestCreationWeek
description: Returns how many weeks ago is the newest date of pull request creation.

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description:
the number of weeks since `start` the newest pull request was created at as an integer
rounded down

name: getCreatedRequestsForPrevWeek
description: Returns an array of all {@link PullRequest} objects which were created on a given week

params.name: weeksAgo
params.description:
which week to return PRs for, as an integer count of weeks from
`start` rounded down

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: pull requests which were created during the given week

name: getMergedRequestsForPrevWeek
description: Returns an array of all {@link PullRequest} objects which were merged on a given week

params.name: weeksAgo
params.description:
which week to return PRs for, as an integer count of weeks from
`start` rounded down

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: pull requests which were merged during the given week

name: getMeanCreationToMergeDaysForMergedPrevWeek
description:
Returns the arithmetic mean of days from creation to merge for all pull requests which were
merged on a given week.

params.name: weeksAgo
params.description:
which week to analyze, as an integer count of weeks from
`start` rounded down

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: pull requests which were merged during the given week

name: src/PullRequest.js
PullRequest
description:
PullRequest is a class representing each GitHub pull request and is generated by
{@link PullExplorer}. It contains properties and methods to access and analyze data associated
with the pull request, including a number of convenience methods for the time since a particular
pull request event has occurred.

name: constructor
description:
PullRequest is a class representing each GitHub pull request and is generate by
{@link PullExplorer}.

params.name: rawJsonData
params.description:
The raw JSON object for a pull request returned by https://api.github.org
per the GitHub v3 API specification

name: createdAt
description: the moment at which this pull request was created.

name: wasMerged
description: whether this pull request has been merged.

name: mergedAt
description:
mergedAt the moment at which this pull request was merged. This property is undefined
if the pull request has not been merged.

name: creationToMergeDays
description:
Returns the number of days from the time of the PR's creation to its merge, if a merge occurred.
If a merge has not happened, an exception is thrown.

return.description: the days between mergedAt and createdAt.

throws.description: if the pull request has not been merged

name: getWeeksPastCreation
description: Returns the number of weeks since this pull request was created

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: the number of weeks since `start` that this pull request was created

name: getWeeksPastMerge
description: Returns the number of weeks since this pull request was merged

unknown.tagValue: {Error} if the pull request has not been merged

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: the number of weeks since `start` that this pull request was merged

name: isCreationBefore
description: Returns whether another pull request is after this one.

params.name: start
params.description: the date at which to calculate from (now by default)

return.description: true if this pull request was created before `other`
